ts.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/26/DSC05999.jpg" /><br /><br />CINCINNATI – The No. 12 West Virginia University baseball team dropped the series finale to Cincinnati, 7-5, Sunday afternoon at UC Baseball Stadium. The Mountaineers fall to 28-12 overall and 13-8 in the Big 12 while the Bearcats improve 29-17 and 10-11 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/26/DSC05999.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/26/DSC05999.jpg"><media:title>Dawson Montesa</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/26/DSC05999.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 18:05:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59047</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>